        <title xml:id="spp-062-1101-title-1">The DISCOVERY <ref target="#spp-062-1101-footnote-title-1">1</ref><note n="1" xml:id="spp-062-1101-footnote-title-1" place="foot">When the Earl of <hi rend="italics">Berkeley</hi> was sent to <hi rend="italics">Ireland</hi> as one of the Lords Justices, the Author, in Compliance with his Invitation, went over with him as Chaplain and private Secretary. But <hi rend="italics">Bush</hi>, another of the Earl's Attendants, having insinuated, that the Place of Secretary was not proper for a Clergyman, found Means, soon after they arrived at <hi rend="italics">Dublin</hi>, to obtain it for himself.────<hi rend="italics">Swift</hi> fired with Indignation at his injurious Treatment, writ this satirical Copy of Verses</note>.</title>
